This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.

Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:
   - Diagnose and fix app-not-visible-in-launcher issue on Galaxy Watch 7 after APK install
   - Investigate rLens (the glasses device itself) consuming more battery when connected to Wear OS vs Garmin
   - Apply CONNECTION_PRIORITY_LOW_POWER to reduce rLens radio wake frequency
   - Fix critical security issue: BLE device binding to prevent connecting to strangers' rLens devices in group runs
   - Apply device name binding to all three apps: runvision-wear, runvision (Flutter), runvision-iq (Garmin)
   - Reduce scan timeout from 10s to 3s
   - Implement 2-retry + automatic new device registration mode: scan saved device 3s×2, if both fail → enter new device mode and scan any rLens 3s×2

2. Key Technical Concepts:
   - BLE connection interval: HIGH=7.5ms (133 radio wakes/sec on rLens), BALANCED=30-100ms, LOW_POWER=100-500ms
   - BLE Peripheral (rLens) follows Central's (watch) connection interval — Central controls peripheral power
   - Samsung One UI Watch hides apps force-stopped via `am force-stop` from launcher — use only `adb install -r`
   - Health Connect permissions (`android.permission.health.READ_HEART_RATE`) cannot be granted via `pm grant`, require Health Connect UI
   - MAC address binding: save first-connected device's MAC/name to SharedPreferences/Application.Storage, only connect to that device on subsequent runs
   - Monkey C `"\0"` escape breaks lexer (treats rest of file as string literal content)
   - Kotlin trailing lambda syntax conflicts with named parameters — must use explicit named parameter for lambda
   - BLE advertising interval: 100-250ms typical → 3 seconds is generous enough for reliable scan
   - 2-retry + new device mode: safe because rLens is always worn before app launch (2 failures = new device scenario)

3. Files and Code Sections:

   - **`runvision-wear/app/src/main/kotlin/com/runvision/wear/ble/RLensConnection.kt`**
     - Changed `CONNECTION_PRIORITY_BALANCED` → `CONNECTION_PRIORITY_LOW_POWER`
     ```kotlin
     // LOW_POWER: 100~500ms 간격 → 5초 전송 주기에서 rLens 라디오 절감 최대화
     val priorityResult = gatt.requestConnectionPriority(BluetoothGatt.CONNECTION_PRIORITY_LOW_POWER)
     ```

   - **`runvision-wear/app/src/main/kotlin/com/runvision/wear/ble/RLensScanner.kt`**
     - Added `targetAddress: String?` parameter for MAC binding
     - In `onScanResult`: skips non-matching devices when `targetAddress` is set
     ```kotlin
     class RLensScanner(
         private val context: Context,
         private val onDeviceFound: (BluetoothDevice) -> Unit,
         private val targetAddress: String? = null
     ) {
         // In onScanResult callback:
         if (targetAddress != null && device.address != targetAddress) {
             Log.d(TAG, "Skipping ${device.name} (${device.address}) — not saved device")
             return
         }
     ```
     - Scan mode remains `SCAN_MODE_LOW_LATENCY` (fast scan, short duration)

   - **`runvision-wear/app/src/main/kotlin/com/runvision/wear/service/ExerciseService.kt`**
     - Added `PREFS_NAME` and `KEY_RLENS_ADDRESS` constants in companion object
     - Modified `initializeBle()` to load/save MAC address from SharedPreferences
     - Changed `SCAN_TIMEOUT_MS`: 10000L → 3000L
     ```kotlin
     companion object {
         const val PREFS_NAME = "runvision_prefs"
         const val KEY_RLENS_ADDRESS = "rlens_mac_address"
     }

     private fun initializeBle() {
         val prefs = getSharedPreferences(PREFS_NAME, android.content.Context.MODE_PRIVATE)
         val savedAddress = prefs.getString(KEY_RLENS_ADDRESS, null)
         Log.d(TAG, "Saved rLens address: ${savedAddress ?: "none (first run)"}")

         rLensScanner = RLensScanner(
             context = this,
             targetAddress = savedAddress,
             onDeviceFound = { device ->
                 if (savedAddress == null) {
                     prefs.edit().putString(KEY_RLENS_ADDRESS, device.address).apply()
                     Log.d(TAG, "Saved rLens address: ${device.address}")
                 }
                 scanTimeoutJob?.cancel()
                 rLensConnection?.connect(device)
             }
         )
     }

     private val SCAN_TIMEOUT_MS = 3000L  // 3 seconds
     ```

   - **`runvision/lib/features/ilens/presentation/providers/ilens_providers.dart`**
